#-Function--onoff
  Function: onoff
      Desc: echo 1 if 'on', 0 if 'off'
  Synopsis: onoff on|1 || off|0 [defaultval]
          : for ambiguous value, echo 'defaultval' if defined, otherwise echo 0.
   Example: result=$(onoff off 1)
    Source: /usr/share/okusi/entities/entities.bash
#-Function--onoff-------------------------------------------------------------
